# Huginn Shared Data Model â€” Schema Specification

## Top-Level Structure

```json
{
  "huginnVersion": "2.0",
  "tasks": [],
  "projects": [],
  "milestones": [],
  "dependencies": [],
  "calendarEvents": [],
  "timekeeping": {
    "activities": [],
    "activeActivityId": null
  }
}
```

All collections use **integer IDs** generated via `Date.now()` (matching existing convention).

---

## Entity Definitions

### Task

A task is the atomic unit of work. Tasks cannot be further decomposed â€” if broken down, they become a project.

```json
{
  "id": 1742860800000,
  "text": "Draft Q2 report",
  "description": "Include KPI summary and risk section",
  "status": "new",
  "createdAt": "2026-03-25T00:00:00.000Z",
  "startedAt": null,
  "finishedAt": null,
  "projectId": null,
  "effort": 1,
  "order": 1.0,
  "nextActionDate": "2026-03-28",
  "deadline": null,
  "estimatedDurationDays": 1,
  "startDate": null,
  "startDateType": "flexible",
  "endDate": null,
  "endDateType": "flexible",
  "scheduledStart": null,
  "scheduledEnd": null
}
```

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `status` | `"new" \| "started" \| "done" \| "stopped"` | Core states. Derived states (blocked, blocker, running late) computed at runtime |
| `projectId` | `int \| null` | Parent project. `null` â†’ auto-assigned to "Personal Tasks" L1 project |
| `effort` | `int â‰Ą 1` | Relative effort estimate |
| `order` | `float` | Sort order within context |
| `startDateType` / `endDateType` | `"flexible" \| "fixed" \| "target"` | Scheduler constraint type |
| `scheduledStart` / `scheduledEnd` | `string \| null` | Computed by scheduler, written on export |
| `startedAt` | `ISO string \| null` | Timestamp when status changed to "started" |

### Project

A project contains tasks, milestones, and subprojects. Every project automatically gets a start milestone, end milestone, and default task on creation.

```json
{
  "id": 1742860800001,
  "name": "Q2 Planning",
  "parentId": null,
  "layer": 1,
  "startMilestoneId": 1742860800010,
  "endMilestoneId": 1742860800011,
  "defaultTaskId": 1742860800012
}
```

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `parentId` | `int \| null` | Parent project ID. `null` = root (L1) project |
| `layer` | `int â‰Ą 1` | Hierarchy depth. Auto-computed from parent chain |
| `startMilestoneId` | `int` | Auto-created start milestone |
| `endMilestoneId` | `int` | Auto-created end milestone |
| `defaultTaskId` | `int` | Auto-created "do $projectname" task |

### Milestone

Milestones are zero-duration events within a project.

```json
{
  "id": 1742860800010,
  "name": "Q2 Planning Start",
  "projectId": 1742860800001,
  "type": "start",
  "date": null,
  "dateType": "flexible",
  "scheduledDate": null
}
```

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `type` | `"start" \| "end" \| "custom"` | Auto-created milestones are [start](file:///Users/yurybodrov/Documents/huginn/experimental/huginn%20tasks%20v7.4.html#602-622)/[end](file:///Users/yurybodrov/Documents/huginn/experimental/huginn%20timekeeper%20v0.1.html#450-456) |
| `dateType` | `"flexible" \| "fixed" \| "target"` | Constraint for scheduler |

### Dependency

Defines ordering constraints between tasks and milestones.

```json
{
  "id": 1742860800020,
  "fromId": 1742860800010,
  "fromType": "milestone",
  "toId": 1742860800000,
  "toType": "task",
  "type": "start"
}
```

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `fromType` / `toType` | `"task" \| "milestone"` | What kind of entity is referenced |
| `type` | `"start"` | `"start"` = [to](file:///Users/yurybodrov/Documents/huginn/experimental/huginn%20tasks%20v7.4.html#649-650) cannot start before `from` finishes |

**Default dependencies** (auto-created with project):
- Start milestone â†’ every task in the project (`type: "start"`)
- Every task â†’ end milestone (`type: "start"`)

### Calendar Event

Full-day events not tied to tasks/projects.

```json
{
  "id": 1742860800030,
  "date": "2026-03-25",
  "type": "vacation",
  "label": "Spring break"
}
```

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `type` | `string` | `vacation`, `trip`, `sick`, `overtime`, `holiday`, `mobile`, `event` |
| `label` | `string \| null` | Optional descriptive label |

Multi-day events are stored as **one entry per day** (same as current Cal v1.0 convention) with the same label to group them.

### Timekeeping Activity

```json
{
  "id": 1742860800040,
  "projectId": 1742860800001,
  "taskId": null,
  "start": "2026-03-25T09:00:00.000Z",
  "end": "2026-03-25T10:30:00.000Z",
  "edited": false
}
```

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `projectId` | `int` | Which project this time is logged against |
| `taskId` | `int \| null` | Optionally track time against a specific task |
| `edited` | `bool` | Auto-set when timestamps are manually changed |

---

## Special Behaviors

### "Personal Tasks" Project
- Auto-created as an L1 project if it doesn't exist
- All tasks with `projectId: null` are treated as belonging to this project
- Has a fixed well-known name: `"Personal Tasks"`

### Preserving Unknown Data
When a component imports the JSON but only uses a subset of collections, it must:
1. Parse the full JSON
2. Modify only the collections it owns
3. Re-serialize the full JSON on export, preserving untouched collections

---

## Migration from Existing Data Models

### Tasks v7.4 â†’ v2.0
- `status: "open"` â†’ `status: "new"`
- `status: "completed"` â†’ `status: "done"`
- `category` field â†’ dropped (replaced by `projectId`)
- Add new fields with defaults: `startedAt: null`, `estimatedDurationDays: 1`, `*DateType: "flexible"`, `scheduledStart/End: null`

### Cal v1.0 â†’ v2.0
- Existing `{ "YYYY-MM-DD": "status" }` map â†’ array of `calendarEvents` objects
- Each key-value pair becomes `{ id, date: key, type: value, label: null }`

### Timekeeper v0.1 â†’ v2.0
- `data.projects` â†’ merge into top-level `projects` array
- `data.activities` â†’ merge into `timekeeping.activities`
- Timekeeper's own project hierarchy preserved via `parentId` references
